  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the Environment for Vulnerable Children in Goma [Eastern DRC]</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has suffered more than 2 decades of conflict: an estimated 5.4 million people have fled their homes, children have been recruited into the armed forces, and acts of sexual violence have been used as a weapon of war. The civil war officially ended with a peace deal in 2003 but the situation remains volatile. Recent months have seen a resurgence of the crisis in some parts of the country with increased displacements of people away from their homes. Growing numbers of children are being forced onto the streets by conflict, displacement, family breakdown and domestic violence &#x2013; girls are especially vulnerable to exploitation and abuse in such circumstances. The project will set up community child protection committees and peer outreach groups so that over 5000 children have someone to turn to in their own communities if abuse occurs. It will provide intensive support to 250 girls who need special help to recover from the abuses they have suffered. Staff working for government departments and charities in the area will be given the knowledge and skills they need to better protect children in the future.</narrative>
  </description>
